A recent survey in urban Shanghai revealed high obesity rates among adults and children, mirroring global trends.
Improved living standards contribute to the rise, with sedentary lifestyles and unhealthy diets as key factors.
In Beijing, overweight individuals lack exercise and consume high-fat foods.
Men face higher obesity risks than women, especially in certain age groups.
In Kuwait, hypnotism proves effective in treating obesity, while poor eating habits lead to widespread obesity and anemia.
Worldwide, diabetes cases are projected to double by 2025 due to aging populations, poor diets, and sedentary lifestyles.
